d to convey meaningfully the reality of the metropolis, the city had to be re-created or reimagined. His book probes the literary response to changing realities of the period and contributes significantly to our understanding of the history of the Western imagination.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aCities and towns in literature. 0aEuropean fictionxHistory and criticismx19th century. 0aEuropean fictionxHistory and criticismx20th century. 0aEuropean fictiony19th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aEuropean fictiony20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aRoman européenxHistoire et critiquex19e siècle. 0aRoman européenxHistoire et critiquex20e siècle. 0aVilles dans la littérature. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066772108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press eBook Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300127072423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300127072.jpg  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press eBook Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  a978-3-11-066772-1  YUP eBook-Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles